PoH and PoF are not quickly accessable zones where you can just sit there and wait.  Both require a raid to effectively clear and engage for the most part, where Rage can be watched by a solo cleric.<br>
<br>
<br>
_____________________<br>
2. Most people cannot afford to take two weeks of RL to sit in one spot waiting for one mob to spawn. This is 24 hours a day for two weeks. This takes into account sitting there while the cleric infront of you gets their Ragefire.<br>
_____________________<br>
<br>
Agreed.... but this is where guild help is almost essential.  I'll use Syllie as an example.  She works 40 hours a week, so she changed her password, and will have people from LM and DoSG keeping her logging in 24-7 the week leading up to her shot at Rage (and the week before that, we'll have 1-2 groups in SF as often as possible).  The day we hope that he pops, many of us will be taking the day off of work to spend the entire day there, which should discourage any other parties from rushing in to take the spawn away from her.<br>
<br>
<br>
______________________<br>
3. The cleric camping it should have full force their with them while waiting for Rage to spawn. This is only an opinion, but there is no other way to ensure you get Rage when he pops if you dont keep full force there. Just having a few cleric friends there is not really enough. I am sorry, but if my guild was not there with me, it would really bug me. And it also shows you what thier priorities are. I know, they can be there in 10-15 mins. But in that time, someone with force there could be done and on the way out.<br>
